com.pixolus.meterreading

Class MeterReadingResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pixolus.meterreading.MeterReadingResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parcelable

    public class MeterReadingResult
extends Object
implements Parcelable
    The MeterReadingResult represents the value of a scanned counter plus metadata.

    In addition to the actual value that consists of integer digits and fraction digits, the class also holds information on how this value was generated and which string was returned by the OCR. The latter (available via rawReadingString()) can contain the character "*" to represent those digits that could not be read by OCR.

    Some examples for values returned by methods of this class are given in the table below. The first column shows a sequence of digits that are assumed to be visible on an actual counter. The second column shows the result returned from rawReadingString(), digits that could not be read reliably by OCR are represented as asterisk characters ("*"). The third column shows the return value of cleanReadingString() for this case. The fourth column shows the return value of status().

    Examples of strings returned by instances of this class:
    Physical data on a counter with 5.3 digits rawReadingString() cleanReadingString() status()
    01234.567"01234.567""1234.567"OK
    01234.567"01234.56*""1234.56"OK
    01234.567"01234.5*7""1234.5"OK_REDUCED_PRECISION
    01234.567"01234.*67""1234"OK_REDUCED_PRECISION
    01234.567"0123*.567"""PARTIAL_READING
    01234.567"*1234.567"""PARTIAL_READING
    01234.567"*1234.56*"""PARTIAL_READING
    01234.567 (counter was found but no clear reading)""""NO_OCR
    01234.567 (no counter found)""""NO_METER_FOUND
    00000.000"00000.000""0.000"OK
    00000.000"00000.0*0""0.0"OK_REDUCED_PRECISION
    00000.000"00000.*00""0"OK_REDUCED_PRECISION
    00000.000"0000*.000"""PARTIAL_READING

      • rawReadingString

        @Nonnull
public String rawReadingString()
        Return a string representing all digits on the meter, including placeholder characters for digits that could not be read reliably.

        The string returned by this method is a representation of the output from the OCR. It is composed of characters from the set 0-9, optionally contains a period character '.' indicating the decimal point of the reading if the counter was configured to contain at least one fractional digit, and with an asterisk character '*' for all digits on the counter that could not be read reliably.

        Examples of possible return values are given in MeterReadingResult.

        Returns:
        a string representing the OCR result.

      • rawReadingString

        @Nonnull
public String rawReadingString(long requiredFractionDigits,
                                        boolean removeLeadingIntegerZeros)
        Implemented identical to rawReadingString(), except that it truncates the result to a required precision (number of fraction digits) and optionally strips leading zeros in the integer part.
        Parameters:
        requiredFractionDigits - The exact number of fraction digits required.
        removeLeadingIntegerZeros - A boolean value specifying whether leading zeros in the integer part will be removed. Note that if the integer part consists of zeros only, a single zero character will remain in the integer part.
        Returns:
        a string representing the OCR result with the requested number of fraction digits, and optionally with leading zeros removed from the integer part.

      • cleanReadingString

        @Nonnull
public String cleanReadingString()
        Return a string representing the value of the counter as read by OCR.

        The returned string represents the numerical value of a counter than could be read by OCR with high confidence. If one or more integer digits on the meter could not be read (including leading zeros if shown on the counter), this method returns an empty string (""). If not the empty string, this string is composed of characters from the set of digits 0-9 and may include one period character '.' indicating the decimal point of the reading value. Leading zeros are removed from the string, except if the integer part of the reading is zero, in which case a single zero character is present for the integer part. The fractional part contains all digits up to the first one which could not reliably read by OCR.

        Examples of possible return values are given in MeterReadingResult.

        Returns:
        the readable part of the counter, or an empty string if one or more integer digits could not be read.

      • cleanReadingString

        @Nonnull
public String cleanReadingString(long requiredFractionDigits)
        Implemented identical to cleanReadingString(), except that it truncates the result to a required precision (number of fraction digits).

        If the clean reading string contains fewer fraction digits than requiredFractionDigits, the method will return an empty string;

        Parameters:
        requiredFractionDigits - The exact number of fraction digits required.
        Returns:
        readable part of the counter with the requested number of fraction digits, or an empty string if not enough digits could be read

      • OBISCode

        @Nonnull
public String OBISCode()
        Return a string representing the OBIS code of the counter as read by OCR.

        When MeterAppearance.LCD_EDL21 is set using the MeterReadingFragment.setMeterAppearance(com.pixolus.meterreading.MeterAppearance) method, the returned value may contain a string of the form "180", or an empty string if no OBIS code could be read. For all other values of MeterAppearance, an empty string is returned.

        Returns:
        OBIS code of the counter, or an empty string if no OBIS code has been read for this counter.

      • status

        @Nonnull
public MeterReadingResult.Status status()
        Return a value detailing the status of the reading result for a counter.

        The status identifies whether the counter could be successfully or partially read, whether a counter was found but OCR could not read the counter or no counter was found at all.

        Note that this status applies to the counter value only. It does not give an indication of whether an OBIS code could be read when MeterAppearance.LCD_EDL21 was set using the MeterReadingFragment.setMeterAppearance(com.pixolus.meterreading.MeterAppearance) method. Instead you should check whether OBISCode() returns an empty string.

        Examples of possible return values are given in MeterReadingResult.

        Returns:
        the status of the OCR result.
        See Also:
        MeterReadingResult.Status

      • lostFractionPrecision

        public long lostFractionPrecision()
        Return the number of fraction digits that are not returned as part of a clean reading. I.e. how much precision of the value on the counter was lost because one or more fractional digits could not be reliably read.

        The reading value as returned by cleanReadingString() contains only the fractional digits up to the first fractional digit that could not be read reliably. This method returns the number of fractional digits on the meter (counting from the right-most, least significant digit) that are not returned as part of the values returned by cleanReadingString().

        Examples of possible return values are given in MeterReadingResult.

        Returns:
        the number of digits that were lost due to one or more digits that could not be read reliably.
